get_stems
---------

This method converts a list of files to a dctionary
	keys are file "stems"
		the "stem" of "alan/was/here.txt" is "here"
	values are a list of all the files with the same stem

	>>> stems = ly.get_stems(files)
	>>> show( stems['ly'] )
	[path('ly.fail'),
	 path('ly.py'),
	 path('ly.pyc'),
	 path('ly.test'),
	 path('ly.tests')]

filter_stems
------------
This method removes all keys from a stems dictionary
	which do not have at least one file with a sought extension


The test depends on this file
	>>> path('trace.log').isfile()
	True

trace.log exists, so "trace" must be a stem
	>>> 'trace' in stems
	True

But we are only interested in python files
	So, after we filter, "trace" is no longer a stem
	>>> ly.filter_stems(stems)
	>>> 'trace' in stems
	False

But ly still is a stem
	>>> show( stems['ly'] )
	[path('ly.fail'),
	 path('ly.py'),
	 path('ly.pyc'),
	 path('ly.test'),
	 path('ly.tests')]

